Rating: 3
This recipe results in a very crispy duck skin and the sauce is tangy and delicious. It's also quite easy. A nice way to make duck that isn't sweet like so many recipes.

Rating: 4
Yummy! I made this recipe this evening and my husband and I thought it was fabulous. The sauce is lovely in combination with the duck. I also followed the idea of another reviewer and deglazed the pan I cooked the duck in with cognac, scraping up the brown bits. I then poured that into the sauce. I definitely will make this recipe again and highly suggest it to everyone.

