very good. I deglazed the pan with cognac and added it to the sauce. not bad, not bad at all.

Rating: 3
I've made this a couple of times and have enjoyed it immensely. Maybe it's just me, but there seems to be a trick to getting the skin really crispy, and I haven't mastered it yet. No matter, it's still pretty good. Also substituted black peppercorns in the sauce, and I thought it came out great.

Rating: 3
I have made this dish several times-- very easy but delicious! You really have to be careful on searing the duck, depending on your stove. I had a gas stove the 1st time I made it, and it was very effortless. Having used an electric stove, I had a much more difficult time controlling the heat as well, so the heat has to be adjusted down (in the initial preheat). This one's impressive!

Rating: 3
This is a fast, easy recipe that has received rave reviews from someone who isn't crazy about duck.